1
00:00:01,000 --> 00:00:32,700
--== McEphie ==--

2
00:00:12,011 --> 00:00:14,848
{\an8}[upbeat music playing]

3
00:00:14,931 --> 00:00:18,101
{\an8}[chanting softly]

4
00:00:21,146 --> 00:00:23,606
{\an8}[ticking]

5
00:00:28,236 --> 00:00:29,904
{\an8}[man in English] Good morning!

6
00:00:29,988 --> 00:00:31,698
{\an8}Rise and shine!

7
00:00:31,781 --> 00:00:33,283
{\an8}Beat you again!

8
00:00:33,366 --> 00:00:37,454
[satisfied groan, yawning]

9
00:00:44,085 --> 00:00:45,587
[shower water running]

10
00:00:48,590 --> 00:00:49,716
Dad! Towel!

11
00:00:50,341 --> 00:00:53,094
Bela, get your brother his towel.

12
00:00:53,678 --> 00:00:55,346
Miss George, towel, please!

13
00:00:55,430 --> 00:00:57,015
[loudly] Benedict, towel!

14
00:00:59,517 --> 00:01:03,521
Oh, that's me. Sorry. Towel, coming!
[chuckles]

15
00:01:04,314 --> 00:01:06,608
[upbeat music resumes]

16
00:01:10,320 --> 00:01:12,447
[sizzling]

17
00:01:14,532 --> 00:01:16,493
-Is this everything?
-[Miss George] Yes.

18
00:01:18,203 --> 00:01:19,829
[Benedict] Bela, Dad, let's eat.

19
00:01:35,011 --> 00:01:35,970
[grunting]

20
00:01:37,597 --> 00:01:38,431
[screaming]

21
00:01:39,599 --> 00:01:41,518
-[game playing]
-Hey, we have to go.

22
00:01:42,101 --> 00:01:43,311
One moment. Wait!

23
00:01:43,895 --> 00:01:45,897
[Dad] I can’t beat your sister yet.

24
00:01:46,856 --> 00:01:49,067
Dad, you really can’t beat her.

25
00:01:49,150 --> 00:01:50,026
Why?

26
00:01:50,110 --> 00:01:51,736
You're using this.

27
00:01:51,820 --> 00:01:53,071
But your score's high.

28
00:01:54,531 --> 00:01:55,865
Come on. Let's go.

29
00:01:59,536 --> 00:02:00,620
I miss you so much.

30
00:02:01,329 --> 00:02:04,541
-[in English] Happy birthday.
-The restroom's so far.

31
00:02:06,000 --> 00:02:07,085
Ah…

32
00:02:08,002 --> 00:02:10,171
-Happy birth--
-Let's go. I'm running late.

33
00:02:10,255 --> 00:02:12,715
[in English] Happy birthday, okay?
Happy birthday!

34
00:02:12,799 --> 00:02:16,136
-[cheerful music playing]
-[whistling softly]

35
00:02:21,432 --> 00:02:22,642
[engine revving]

36
00:02:22,725 --> 00:02:24,227
[car horn honking]

37
00:02:33,570 --> 00:02:36,489
Good evening to all my peeps out there

38
00:02:36,573 --> 00:02:39,159
who are listening
to our live podcast tonight.

39
00:02:39,242 --> 00:02:41,786
This is Papa Tak.

40
00:02:41,870 --> 00:02:44,622
I'm here to solve your love problems.

41
00:02:44,706 --> 00:02:48,418
The time is eight o'clock in the evening.

42
00:02:48,501 --> 00:02:53,214
We will now start
our conversation with Papa Tak!

43
00:02:53,298 --> 00:02:56,509
-Our first caller.
-[caller] <i>Hello, Papa Tak. This is Helen.</i>

44
00:02:56,593 --> 00:02:59,721
[in English] <i>I've had a boyfriend</i>
<i>for five years now.</i>

45
00:02:59,804 --> 00:03:02,265
<i>We haven't had any problems so far.</i>

46
00:03:02,348 --> 00:03:05,393
<i>Helen! So why did you call</i>
<i>when you don't have any problem?</i>

47
00:03:05,476 --> 00:03:07,061
[Hugot Tina]
<i>That's her problem.</i>

48
00:03:07,145 --> 00:03:11,024
<i>Good that she doesn't have any problems</i>
<i>while others have lots of it.</i>

49
00:03:11,107 --> 00:03:12,734
<i>Here's what you need to do.</i>

50
00:03:12,817 --> 00:03:16,112
<i>Call me once you have</i>
<i>a problem, okay? Next!</i>

51
00:03:16,738 --> 00:03:19,532
[caller 2] <i>Hello, Papa Tak, this is Jun.</i>

52
00:03:19,616 --> 00:03:21,409
-<i>I have a question.</i>
-<i>Yes, Jun?</i>

53
00:03:21,492 --> 00:03:22,785
<i>I would like to know</i>

54
00:03:22,869 --> 00:03:25,330
<i>when the girl I am courting</i>
<i>will finally say yes.</i>

55
00:03:25,413 --> 00:03:26,956
<i>Jun, let me remind you.</i>

56
00:03:27,040 --> 00:03:28,625
<i>I'm a DJ, not a fortune-teller.</i>

57
00:03:28,708 --> 00:03:31,169
<i>Ask the girl you're courting, not me.</i>

58
00:03:31,252 --> 00:03:34,172
<i>And Jun, if you really want to know,</i>
<i>go to Quiapo.</i>

59
00:03:34,255 --> 00:03:38,259
<i>Ask the fortune-teller, and also,</i>
<i>ask when you two will break up. Next!</i>

60
00:03:38,343 --> 00:03:41,095
<i>I prefer someone</i>
<i>not too beautiful but kind,</i>

61
00:03:41,179 --> 00:03:43,765
<i>obedient, hardworking, thoughtful,</i>

62
00:03:43,848 --> 00:03:46,684
<i>who knows how to cook,</i>
<i>and who can do chores.</i>

63
00:03:46,768 --> 00:03:49,938
<i>Zaldy, you aren’t looking for a girlfriend</i>

64
00:03:50,021 --> 00:03:53,316
but a house help. Tell us if you want her
to stay in or stay out.

65
00:03:53,399 --> 00:03:55,318
[laughing]

66
00:03:55,818 --> 00:03:58,196
Before we continue with our program,

67
00:03:58,279 --> 00:04:00,448
I want to introduce my co-host first,

68
00:04:00,531 --> 00:04:01,991
who's been speaking her mind.

69
00:04:02,075 --> 00:04:03,785
Here's Hugot Tina!

70
00:04:03,868 --> 00:04:05,912
[voice echoes]

71
00:04:05,995 --> 00:04:08,748
Good evening, Papa Tak.
To our listeners this evening,

72
00:04:08,831 --> 00:04:12,919
I'm the girl who speaks my mind
out here, there, and everywhere!

73
00:04:13,002 --> 00:04:15,713
My name is Hugot Tina.

74
00:04:15,797 --> 00:04:17,966
[staff yelling]

75
00:04:18,049 --> 00:04:20,218
Good evening to you too, Hugot Tina.

76
00:04:20,301 --> 00:04:24,097
And now, let's continue
our conversation with Papa Tak.

77
00:04:24,180 --> 00:04:25,807
Next caller, please.

78
00:04:27,267 --> 00:04:28,268
[woman] Hi.

79
00:04:28,851 --> 00:04:32,063
[Hugot Tina]
And for our next caller, here she is!

80
00:04:32,563 --> 00:04:35,525
[caller 3] <i>Hugot Tina,</i>
<i>Can you help me with my boyfriend?</i>

81
00:04:35,608 --> 00:04:37,277
[Hugot Tina]
Why? How old are you?

82
00:04:37,360 --> 00:04:39,737
[caller] <i>Twenty-one.</i>
<i>He’s my first boyfriend.</i>

83
00:04:39,821 --> 00:04:42,156
-[Hugot Tina] How old is he?
-[indistinct]

84
00:04:42,240 --> 00:04:45,535
-[Hugot Tina] This is what you should do…
-[in English] Thank you!

85
00:04:48,746 --> 00:04:50,915
[man in English] One coffee for Papa Tak.

86
00:04:50,999 --> 00:04:52,667
No, thank you.

87
00:04:52,750 --> 00:04:53,918
No, it's mine.

88
00:04:54,711 --> 00:04:56,587
Babe, why are you late?

89
00:04:57,171 --> 00:04:59,215
I already started with my podcast.

90
00:04:59,299 --> 00:05:01,342
I thought you’d be off by 5 p.m.

91
00:05:01,426 --> 00:05:02,719
[in English] Babe, sorry.

92
00:05:03,344 --> 00:05:05,722
My boss talked to me.

93
00:05:05,805 --> 00:05:09,100
That's right. My boss talked to her.
It took so long.

94
00:05:10,476 --> 00:05:11,853
Is it about your promotion?

95
00:05:12,437 --> 00:05:14,897
Babe. Please let me accept it.

96
00:05:14,981 --> 00:05:16,649
You should be happy for me.

97
00:05:17,317 --> 00:05:18,401
[sighs]

98
00:05:19,027 --> 00:05:20,778
I am happy for you, babe.

99
00:05:21,362 --> 00:05:23,448
Babe. It's just Singapore.

100
00:05:24,115 --> 00:05:27,827
I can go home every weekend
or you can visit me there.

101
00:05:28,661 --> 00:05:29,829
[sighs softly] Babe.

102
00:05:30,330 --> 00:05:32,206
Singapore or any country,

103
00:05:32,707 --> 00:05:33,875
you’d still be leaving.

104
00:05:35,376 --> 00:05:37,086
We will still be apart.

105
00:05:38,171 --> 00:05:39,922
That's what I'm asking you…

106
00:05:40,423 --> 00:05:41,549
not to leave.

107
00:05:44,344 --> 00:05:46,929
And speaking of leaving, I have to leave.

108
00:05:47,013 --> 00:05:48,681
I need to go back to the podcast.

109
00:05:48,765 --> 00:05:51,225
Just wait for me here
and I'll take you home.

110
00:05:51,309 --> 00:05:52,769
No need. We'll go ahead.

111
00:05:53,436 --> 00:05:55,313
Go ahead. I’m only taking her.

112
00:05:57,148 --> 00:05:58,399
[in English] Thank you.

113
00:05:59,525 --> 00:06:00,735
He's sweet, isn’t he?

114
00:06:02,195 --> 00:06:04,489
-Right? Sweet.
-Let's go.

115
00:06:04,572 --> 00:06:05,615
Let's go.

116
00:06:06,657 --> 00:06:08,534
[Benedict]
We'll see us again tomorrow.

117
00:06:08,618 --> 00:06:10,661
Same time, same place.

118
00:06:10,745 --> 00:06:12,955
Only here, on our program with…

119
00:06:13,039 --> 00:06:14,248
Hugot Tina.

120
00:06:14,332 --> 00:06:17,919
And Papa Tak! Goodbye!

121
00:06:18,002 --> 00:06:20,213
-[upbeat music playing]
-[ticking]

122
00:06:25,385 --> 00:06:27,011
-Here, sir.
-Thank you.

123
00:06:33,851 --> 00:06:35,061
[sneezing]

124
00:06:44,737 --> 00:06:45,571
Mm-mm.

125
00:06:50,243 --> 00:06:52,120
Mm-mm.

126
00:07:01,045 --> 00:07:02,213
[gushing]

127
00:07:03,005 --> 00:07:04,006
Mm-hmm.

128
00:07:08,010 --> 00:07:09,262
[murmurs]

129
00:07:10,138 --> 00:07:11,431
[inaudible]

130
00:07:21,899 --> 00:07:24,402
And that's where we end our program,

131
00:07:24,485 --> 00:07:27,029
but we'll see each other again tomorrow.

132
00:07:27,113 --> 00:07:29,240
[in English] Same time, same place.

133
00:07:29,323 --> 00:07:31,159
Only here, on our program with…

134
00:07:31,242 --> 00:07:32,785
[Hugot Tina] Hugot Tina.

135
00:07:32,869 --> 00:07:34,036
And Papa Tak!

136
00:07:34,120 --> 00:07:35,288
[in English] Goodbye!

137
00:07:35,371 --> 00:07:39,208
-[mix instruments playing]
-[staff sings][in English] Bye bye!

138
00:07:39,959 --> 00:07:42,503
Tina, you're late again.

139
00:07:42,587 --> 00:07:44,922
Sorry, there was heavy traffic.

140
00:07:45,006 --> 00:07:47,091
[staff mocking]

141
00:07:47,175 --> 00:07:48,593
But you're always late.

142
00:07:49,427 --> 00:07:52,054
If you leave early,
then you'll get here on time.

143
00:07:52,889 --> 00:07:54,932
-True!
-Know what? If you do that again,

144
00:07:55,516 --> 00:07:56,601
I will replace you!

145
00:07:56,684 --> 00:07:58,394
[staff] Right. Right.

146
00:07:58,477 --> 00:08:01,481
Right? You'll get some hitting too.
You, Jon, Bon, Jovi.

147
00:08:01,564 --> 00:08:02,815
Are you perfect?

148
00:08:03,316 --> 00:08:05,860
We've been doing this for years.
Your timing is still off.

149
00:08:08,279 --> 00:08:09,739
-Sorry, Papa Tak.
-Sorry.

150
00:08:09,822 --> 00:08:12,575
-Sorry, Papa Tak.
-You always say sorry.

151
00:08:13,159 --> 00:08:14,327
Get your act together!

152
00:08:15,411 --> 00:08:18,289
Will you always apologize after each show?

153
00:08:18,789 --> 00:08:20,041
We're always like this.

154
00:08:21,334 --> 00:08:22,501
I'm getting sick of it.

155
00:08:23,002 --> 00:08:25,213
Right, Papa Tak,
we’ll get it right next time.

156
00:08:26,380 --> 00:08:28,674
-Okay, I’ll go ahead.
-Take care.

157
00:08:36,057 --> 00:08:37,183
[sigh]

158
00:08:37,266 --> 00:08:39,435
[atmospheric music playing]

159
00:08:39,519 --> 00:08:40,353
Victoria.

160
00:08:41,646 --> 00:08:43,397
You know what, when you're with me,

161
00:08:44,607 --> 00:08:46,359
my world stops.

162
00:08:47,735 --> 00:08:50,988
That's why I want to give you…

163
00:08:52,490 --> 00:08:53,741
all my time.

164
00:08:55,618 --> 00:08:56,577
Victoria.

165
00:09:00,081 --> 00:09:01,123
Will you marry me?

166
00:09:04,877 --> 00:09:05,795
Papa Tak?

167
00:09:06,379 --> 00:09:07,505
Papa Tak!

168
00:09:07,964 --> 00:09:10,466
[screaming] Papa Tak is here!

169
00:09:10,550 --> 00:09:12,468
It's Papa Tak!

170
00:09:12,552 --> 00:09:14,011
Mother, Papa Tak is here!

171
00:09:14,095 --> 00:09:15,513
-You are my idol!
-Thank you.

172
00:09:15,596 --> 00:09:17,098
-You are my idol!
-Thank you.

173
00:09:17,181 --> 00:09:18,891
-Papa Tak, you are my idol!
-Thank you.

174
00:09:18,975 --> 00:09:20,977
-[in English] Roses?
-Yes, roses.

175
00:09:21,060 --> 00:09:24,146
Wait, I have many stories about that.

176
00:09:24,230 --> 00:09:26,649
Miss, is this seat taken?

177
00:09:26,732 --> 00:09:30,111
-No.
-Can you move here?

178
00:09:30,194 --> 00:09:31,862
[in English] There. Thank you!

179
00:09:31,946 --> 00:09:35,199
You know what, Papa Tak? About the roses.

180
00:09:35,283 --> 00:09:39,245
I gave my girlfriend one of these,

181
00:09:39,328 --> 00:09:41,872
but we still broke up! [sobbing]

182
00:09:41,956 --> 00:09:44,250
-It was just bad luck.
-I’m not unlucky.

183
00:09:44,333 --> 00:09:45,501
I’m not unlucky.

184
00:09:45,584 --> 00:09:47,378
But let's take a selfie first.

185
00:09:48,212 --> 00:09:49,922
-You want to hold it?
-You're crying?

186
00:09:50,423 --> 00:09:53,050
No, I already moved on. That was long ago.

187
00:09:53,134 --> 00:09:54,969
Aren't you listening to my stories?

188
00:09:55,052 --> 00:09:57,847
-Sorry.
-Okay, you take the selfie.

189
00:09:58,806 --> 00:10:02,101
[deep breath]
You're not even that techie, Papa Tak.

190
00:10:02,184 --> 00:10:04,478
-Let's stand to get another angle.
-Stand?

191
00:10:04,562 --> 00:10:06,856
Yes, so we can show the ambiance.

192
00:10:06,939 --> 00:10:09,025
-[in English] Ambiance!
-Ambiance!

193
00:10:09,108 --> 00:10:10,234
[man giggles]

194
00:10:10,318 --> 00:10:12,153
Okay. Now, take a picture of me.

195
00:10:12,236 --> 00:10:15,239
-Ambiance… Yes, for my profile picture.
-Are you sure?

196
00:10:15,323 --> 00:10:18,242
-Yes. Sure.
-Okay.

197
00:10:28,919 --> 00:10:32,006
[romantic music playing]

198
00:10:44,602 --> 00:10:47,438
-Sorry, babe. Am I late again?
-No, babe. It's all right.

199
00:10:48,147 --> 00:10:49,815
Ugh. Babe.

200
00:10:51,108 --> 00:10:52,651
Babe, flowers for you.

201
00:10:58,532 --> 00:10:59,659
[sighs heavily]

202
00:11:02,620 --> 00:11:03,621
Let's order?

203
00:11:03,704 --> 00:11:05,873
I already ordered for us.

204
00:11:11,003 --> 00:11:12,004
[clears throat]

205
00:11:13,839 --> 00:11:14,840
Babe.

206
00:11:16,884 --> 00:11:18,761
It's not my birthday.

207
00:11:20,346 --> 00:11:22,223
And it’s not our anniversary.

208
00:11:25,393 --> 00:11:26,769
What’s the occasion?

209
00:11:27,353 --> 00:11:28,521
Because babe…

210
00:11:29,605 --> 00:11:33,150
-I have something to tell you--
-Wait. Let me talk first.

211
00:11:33,859 --> 00:11:35,653
I also have something to tell you.

212
00:11:36,278 --> 00:11:38,114
[chuckles] Wait, babe,

213
00:11:38,197 --> 00:11:40,658
don't tell me you're breaking up with me.

214
00:11:41,701 --> 00:11:43,494
That only happens in the movies.

215
00:11:45,413 --> 00:11:46,789
Yes, Benedict,

216
00:11:46,872 --> 00:11:48,791
that's what I really want to tell you.

217
00:11:49,834 --> 00:11:52,461
I think it's time for us
to go our separate ways.

218
00:11:53,546 --> 00:11:54,547
Why, babe?

219
00:11:55,506 --> 00:11:58,634
[guitar playing]

220
00:12:02,513 --> 00:12:05,433
[woman]Thank you, honey.

221
00:12:06,392 --> 00:12:10,438
♪ <i>Ask me, ask me</i> ♪

222
00:12:10,521 --> 00:12:13,524
♪ <i>Who I love, who I love</i> ♪

223
00:12:15,401 --> 00:12:17,945
I’m getting tired of our relationship.

224
00:12:19,655 --> 00:12:21,490
You always decide.

225
00:12:22,992 --> 00:12:24,952
You never listen to me.

226
00:12:26,579 --> 00:12:30,458
I feel like you want to control my life.

227
00:12:30,541 --> 00:12:32,376
At first, it was okay because…

228
00:12:34,044 --> 00:12:35,504
because I loved you.

229
00:12:36,130 --> 00:12:37,339
But no.

230
00:12:38,591 --> 00:12:41,260
I don't count in this relationship.

231
00:12:42,511 --> 00:12:46,056
You don't even know
that I don't like it here.

232
00:12:47,641 --> 00:12:51,854
But babe, all our occasions,
our events, we celebrate here.

233
00:12:51,937 --> 00:12:53,647
I thought this was
your favorite restaurant.

234
00:12:53,731 --> 00:12:55,107
Your favorite.

235
00:12:55,983 --> 00:12:58,152
You just assume that I like it here.

236
00:12:59,195 --> 00:13:01,322
I'm allergic to seafood.

237
00:13:01,405 --> 00:13:03,282
[waiter] Excuse me, sir. Your order.

238
00:13:07,578 --> 00:13:08,412
[clears throat]

239
00:13:11,081 --> 00:13:12,249
[clears throat louder]

240
00:13:13,459 --> 00:13:14,794
I'm sorry, Benedict.

241
00:13:16,462 --> 00:13:17,546
Babe.

242
00:13:18,589 --> 00:13:20,341
[in English] You have to let me go.

243
00:13:25,137 --> 00:13:25,971
Babe.

244
00:13:27,556 --> 00:13:30,851
[melancholic music playing]

245
00:13:38,192 --> 00:13:40,736
[thunder rumbling]

246
00:13:40,819 --> 00:13:45,616
-[thunder rumbling continues]
-[crowd chattering]

247
00:13:46,825 --> 00:13:52,540
♪ <i>My aching heart is crying</i>
<i>My aching heart is crying</i> ♪

248
00:13:52,623 --> 00:13:58,379
♪ <i>I don’t want anyone to witness it</i>
<i>I don’t want anyone to witness it</i> ♪

249
00:13:58,462 --> 00:14:02,716
♪ <i>No matter how hurtful it is</i>
<i>No matter how hurtful it is</i> ♪

250
00:14:02,800 --> 00:14:05,427
[thunder rumbling]

251
00:14:05,511 --> 00:14:09,014
♪ <i>I don’t want her to see it</i>
