00:31:32,181 --> 00:31:34,642
Despacito.

520
00:31:34,726 --> 00:31:36,477
Despacito.

521
00:31:39,814 --> 00:31:40,857
[in Spanish] I love you.

522
00:31:41,608 --> 00:31:43,818
I love you with all my heart.

523
00:31:45,069 --> 00:31:47,780
[sobbing] I want to breathe in your neck.

524
00:31:48,907 --> 00:31:50,199
[sobbing]

525
00:31:52,702 --> 00:31:54,454
[in Spanish] I love you!

526
00:31:55,788 --> 00:31:58,166
[heart beating heavily]

527
00:31:58,249 --> 00:31:59,918
[in Spanish] I love you too.

528
00:32:00,001 --> 00:32:05,173
-[sad music playing]
-[panting]

529
00:32:06,507 --> 00:32:07,634
Does it hurt?

530
00:32:07,717 --> 00:32:08,968
Just pick me instead.

531
00:32:10,595 --> 00:32:12,138
[grunts]

532
00:32:12,764 --> 00:32:13,598
[gasping]

533
00:32:13,681 --> 00:32:15,892
Victoria! Victoria?

534
00:32:15,975 --> 00:32:18,061
[rapid breathing]

535
00:32:19,896 --> 00:32:21,856
[gasping] Sir Saro!

536
00:32:21,939 --> 00:32:24,233
Sir Saro! Hi, idol!

537
00:32:24,943 --> 00:32:26,986
Don't talk to him!

538
00:32:27,654 --> 00:32:28,863
Why is he here?

539
00:32:29,572 --> 00:32:31,574
He wants to go back to his past fight!

540
00:32:32,158 --> 00:32:34,118
I see. Can I get an autograph?

541
00:32:34,202 --> 00:32:35,828
Idol! Can I get an autograph?

542
00:32:37,664 --> 00:32:39,040
That's what happened to me?

543
00:32:39,582 --> 00:32:41,334
[stutters] But Sir Saro,

544
00:32:41,417 --> 00:32:43,086
what you were saying is true.

545
00:32:43,169 --> 00:32:44,963
I have been to different eras!

546
00:32:45,505 --> 00:32:47,548
But how did I get back here?

547
00:32:48,424 --> 00:32:49,676
You restarted.

548
00:32:49,759 --> 00:32:52,220
Restart? How? Like a video game?

549
00:32:52,303 --> 00:32:53,471
Exactly!

550
00:32:54,389 --> 00:32:55,807
When you die,

551
00:32:55,890 --> 00:32:57,976
you will go to a different era.

552
00:32:58,559 --> 00:33:01,729
If you couldn't complete your mission,
you will come back to the bar.

553
00:33:01,813 --> 00:33:03,940
What? Why did you just tell me now?

554
00:33:04,023 --> 00:33:07,527
I was supposed to tell you,
but you already drank the Wishkey.

555
00:33:07,610 --> 00:33:10,655
But why do I need to go
to different times?

556
00:33:10,738 --> 00:33:14,450
Why can't I just go back to the time
when Victoria and I broke up?

557
00:33:18,037 --> 00:33:19,831
Because now that you started this,

558
00:33:21,874 --> 00:33:27,880
only the Wishkey knows
where it's power will take you.

559
00:33:27,964 --> 00:33:31,092
What? So it means I have to go
to a lot of different eras?

560
00:33:32,093 --> 00:33:33,177
Now you know!

561
00:33:33,761 --> 00:33:35,054
Oh, come on!

562
00:33:36,055 --> 00:33:36,931
[sighs]

563
00:33:38,599 --> 00:33:39,851
-Sir Saro!
-Huh?

564
00:33:39,934 --> 00:33:41,394
Why does Joey Marquez have a bottle?

565
00:33:41,477 --> 00:33:43,104
-Where?
-There!

566
00:33:43,813 --> 00:33:45,440
I already broke that one!

567
00:33:48,192 --> 00:33:49,277
[grunts]

568
00:33:54,157 --> 00:33:56,284
[gasping]

569
00:34:01,664 --> 00:34:04,083
[classic guitar playing]

570
00:34:05,043 --> 00:34:06,502
[spitting]

571
00:34:11,215 --> 00:34:13,593
-Are you okay?
-Bela?

572
00:34:13,676 --> 00:34:15,678
Why are you here? Where's Dad?

573
00:34:16,387 --> 00:34:17,221
Who's Bela?

574
00:34:17,972 --> 00:34:21,100
I am not Bela. I am Gregoria.

575
00:34:22,310 --> 00:34:23,811
And you. Who are you?

576
00:34:23,895 --> 00:34:26,481
I am… Hua Ze Lei.

577
00:34:27,065 --> 00:34:30,318
-Hua Ze Lei?
-What-che-lei-lei. What-che-lei.

578
00:34:32,695 --> 00:34:33,946
I can't understand you.

579
00:34:35,907 --> 00:34:37,074
Fix it.

580
00:34:37,825 --> 00:34:38,701
How are you?

581
00:34:39,410 --> 00:34:40,453
Victoria!

582
00:34:41,454 --> 00:34:43,998
-I am not Victoria.
-I am Maria.

583
00:34:45,541 --> 00:34:46,626
Excuse me.

584
00:34:48,836 --> 00:34:49,712
Maria.

585
00:34:51,255 --> 00:34:54,884
You need to know something about me,
why I am here.

586
00:34:58,429 --> 00:34:59,555
What do you want?

587
00:35:00,932 --> 00:35:03,226
It's because I'm not from here.

588
00:35:04,185 --> 00:35:07,438
I came from a different time,
and I have a mission.

589
00:35:08,272 --> 00:35:10,608
Because of you, Victoria. I mean, Maria.

590
00:35:10,691 --> 00:35:12,151
You're not from here?

591
00:35:12,235 --> 00:35:14,195
-Are you a spy?
-No!

592
00:35:15,071 --> 00:35:17,949
No, in fact, I love our country.

593
00:35:18,616 --> 00:35:20,493
Um… um…

594
00:35:20,576 --> 00:35:23,579
I am here because you need to love me.

595
00:35:26,666 --> 00:35:28,334
If you're not a spy,

596
00:35:29,210 --> 00:35:31,546
then you're probably crazy.

597
00:35:32,046 --> 00:35:34,340
Yes. I am crazy about you.

598
00:35:34,841 --> 00:35:36,092
Really, now.

599
00:35:36,968 --> 00:35:40,429
If you're telling the truth
and you are not a spy,

600
00:35:40,513 --> 00:35:42,849
prove it in our attack later.

601
00:35:44,058 --> 00:35:46,519
[in English] Attack? Go! Carry.

602
00:35:47,019 --> 00:35:47,895
Comrades!

603
00:35:49,230 --> 00:35:50,106
Um…

604
00:35:51,232 --> 00:35:54,443
Supremo is calling us.

605
00:35:58,573 --> 00:36:01,159
[dark music playing]

606
00:36:04,412 --> 00:36:05,413
Who is he?

607
00:36:06,664 --> 00:36:08,291
-Don’t you know him?
-No.

608
00:36:08,374 --> 00:36:09,959
He is the Supremo.

609
00:36:11,878 --> 00:36:12,879
Supremo?

610
00:36:13,880 --> 00:36:16,591
Why does Richard Gutierrez
look different in person.

611
00:36:18,426 --> 00:36:19,844
Don’t you know the Supremo?

612
00:36:19,927 --> 00:36:21,179
I said I don't.

613
00:36:21,262 --> 00:36:24,473
Supremo is Andres Bonifacio.

614
00:36:26,017 --> 00:36:27,351
Andres Bonifacio!

615
00:36:27,435 --> 00:36:29,353
Sh!

616
00:36:30,188 --> 00:36:32,815
He’s my idol.

617
00:36:38,237 --> 00:36:39,155
Comrades!

618
00:36:41,157 --> 00:36:43,743
Supremo has an important announcement.

619
00:36:46,245 --> 00:36:50,458
[eventful music playing]

620
00:36:51,417 --> 00:36:52,501
Comrades!

621
00:36:54,045 --> 00:36:55,880
The revolution has begun!

622
00:36:59,217 --> 00:37:02,470
Later, our attack is set

623
00:37:03,471 --> 00:37:07,516
to ambush the civil guards
who will cross Balintawak.

624
00:37:11,270 --> 00:37:16,442
We will meet there
the group of Berting, from Hagonoy.

625
00:37:17,568 --> 00:37:19,153
Long live the revolution!

626
00:37:19,237 --> 00:37:20,529
Long live!

627
00:37:20,613 --> 00:37:21,822
Long live the Katipunan!

628
00:37:21,906 --> 00:37:23,658
Long live!

629
00:37:24,241 --> 00:37:26,243
-Long live free WiFi!
-Long live…

630
00:37:26,744 --> 00:37:28,579
Long live freedom of speech…

631
00:37:28,663 --> 00:37:30,373
Wakanda forever!

632
00:37:31,457 --> 00:37:32,792
Sorry about that, Supremo.

633
00:37:35,544 --> 00:37:37,755
Let's take out our daggers!

634
00:37:38,464 --> 00:37:42,009
Let’s show our loyalty to the Katipunan!

635
00:37:42,843 --> 00:37:45,054
[screaming]

636
00:37:45,846 --> 00:37:48,391
[screaming]

637
00:37:50,559 --> 00:37:51,978
[screaming]

638
00:37:52,061 --> 00:37:53,020
Brother!

639
00:37:54,605 --> 00:37:55,982
We're done. We did that yesterday.

640
00:38:05,700 --> 00:38:06,742
Comrades!

641
00:38:08,286 --> 00:38:10,162
Take out your identification cards!

642
00:38:10,246 --> 00:38:12,123
[up-tempo music playing]

643
00:38:16,252 --> 00:38:18,379
Let us all tear our identification cards!

644
00:38:19,338 --> 00:38:20,923
Long live the revolution!

645
00:38:21,007 --> 00:38:22,174
Long live!

646
00:38:22,258 --> 00:38:23,592
Long live the Katipunan!

647
00:38:23,676 --> 00:38:25,052
Long live!

648
00:38:25,136 --> 00:38:26,429
Supremo!

649
00:38:27,805 --> 00:38:28,723
Good news.

650
00:38:28,806 --> 00:38:29,807
What is it, Poochy?

651
00:38:29,890 --> 00:38:31,058
We are getting our firearms!

652
00:38:31,142 --> 00:38:33,269
Good! What do we need?

653
00:38:33,894 --> 00:38:35,146
Our identification cards.

654
00:38:36,480 --> 00:38:38,649
[crickets chirping]

655
00:38:42,069 --> 00:38:44,280
Pick up the identification cards. Hurry!

656
00:38:44,363 --> 00:38:46,574
Double time!
I have one, and it's intact!

657
00:38:46,657 --> 00:38:48,784
That's good. Give it to me.

658
00:38:48,868 --> 00:38:53,372
[tense music playing]

659
00:39:01,714 --> 00:39:03,382
Get ready, comrades.

660
00:39:04,216 --> 00:39:05,384
They're getting closer.

661
00:39:14,894 --> 00:39:18,022
[Benedict] Maria, are you sure
about what you are doing?

662
00:39:18,522 --> 00:39:19,982
[Benedict] This is dangerous.

663
00:39:22,193 --> 00:39:23,486
You are talking nonsense.

664
00:39:24,403 --> 00:39:27,323
I am ready to fight for our freedom.

665
00:39:28,783 --> 00:39:32,536
If that's what you want to do,
then let me be the one to do it for you.

666
00:39:32,620 --> 00:39:33,996
Remember.

667
00:39:34,789 --> 00:39:37,416
[in English] With great power,
comes great…

668
00:39:38,292 --> 00:39:39,418
great…

669
00:39:40,336 --> 00:39:41,921
taste love of all.

670
00:39:42,004 --> 00:39:44,048
And I promise, if you jump, I jump!

671
00:39:46,008 --> 00:39:47,009
They're here.

672
00:39:47,968 --> 00:39:48,969
What?

673
00:39:49,053 --> 00:39:52,640
-The Spaniards are here.
-The Spaniards are here.

674
00:39:55,518 --> 00:39:56,727
Positions, comrades.

675
00:40:03,776 --> 00:40:06,654
Okay, I will follow. I'm almost done.

676
00:40:15,871 --> 00:40:19,500
[suspenseful music playing]

677
00:40:19,583 --> 00:40:20,835
[sword blade scraping]

678
00:40:22,878 --> 00:40:23,754
[clanking]

679
00:40:25,506 --> 00:40:27,800
-[sword blade scraping]
-Alert!

680
00:40:27,883 --> 00:40:31,303
Charge! [screaming]

681
00:40:31,387 --> 00:40:35,015
[intense music playing]

682
00:40:41,230 --> 00:40:44,692
[screaming]

683
00:40:47,278 --> 00:40:48,279
That's right!

684
00:40:48,863 --> 00:40:51,615
[grunting, screaming]

685
00:40:57,204 --> 00:40:59,206
Ouch! Ouch!

686
00:40:59,290 --> 00:41:00,583
[soft instrumental music]

687
00:41:00,666 --> 00:41:02,626
Ouch! Ouch!

688
00:41:04,128 --> 00:41:05,004
Ouch!

689
00:41:05,087 --> 00:41:06,589
-[screams]
-[grunts]

690
00:41:13,429 --> 00:41:14,847
Ouch!

691
00:41:14,930 --> 00:41:16,724
-It's itchy! Itchy!
-[indistinct]

692
00:41:16,807 --> 00:41:19,351
It's itchy! It's so itchy! Ouch!

693
00:41:19,435 --> 00:41:20,519
Horrible.

694
00:41:20,603 --> 00:41:22,730
Hey, can you at least look at it? Please?

695
00:41:22,813 --> 00:41:25,482
[screaming]

696
00:41:25,566 --> 00:41:26,817
Charge!

697
00:41:26,901 --> 00:41:29,111
[screaming]

698
00:41:33,365 --> 00:41:35,534
Brother, let's go.

699
00:41:37,369 --> 00:41:38,579
Oh, is it that way?

700
00:41:39,747 --> 00:41:41,540
[grunting]

701
00:41:41,624 --> 00:41:42,958
[sword blade scraping]

702
00:41:57,890 --> 00:41:59,350
Thank you very much, Berting.

703
00:41:59,934 --> 00:42:02,394
-Anything for our country, Supremo.
-To your positions.

704
00:42:02,978 --> 00:42:04,313
Go! Hurry!

705
00:42:04,897 --> 00:42:05,981
[man] To your positions!

706
00:42:09,485 --> 00:42:11,987
[breathing heavily]

707
00:42:12,071 --> 00:42:14,156
-Let's go, brother.
-You are a Spaniard!

708
00:42:14,740 --> 00:42:15,866
You took her from me!

709
00:42:15,950 --> 00:42:17,535
This is what you deserve!

710
00:42:17,618 --> 00:42:19,411
[grunting]

711
00:42:19,495 --> 00:42:21,497
[man] What are you talking about?

712
00:42:22,081 --> 00:42:23,999
-I'm not Kapatid, I'm Kapamilya!
-Traitor.

713
00:42:24,083 --> 00:42:25,960
Comrades! There's a traitor here!

714
00:42:26,043 --> 00:42:27,670
That's right. There's a traitor!

715
00:42:27,753 --> 00:42:29,547
Why are you fighting Berting?

716
00:42:29,630 --> 00:42:31,131
You're a traitor!

717
00:42:32,341 --> 00:42:33,551
Oh, she's a Kapuso.

718
00:42:35,344 --> 00:42:36,971
[groans]

719
00:42:38,764 --> 00:42:39,765
[Benedict] Victoria!

720
00:42:43,269 --> 00:42:45,271
[Benedict] Thank God, I’m alive.

721
00:42:45,771 --> 00:42:47,481
I really thought you killed me.

722
00:42:48,315 --> 00:42:49,400
[Benedict exhaling]

723
00:42:53,362 --> 00:42:54,780
[Benedict] You’re coming.

724
00:42:57,992 --> 00:43:01,287
At long last, I can finally taste you.

725
00:43:02,121 --> 00:43:03,205
[Benedict] Really?

726
00:43:03,289 --> 00:43:04,498
What are you saying?

727
00:43:04,582 --> 00:43:06,667
You really missed me. [chuckles]

728
00:43:08,627 --> 00:43:10,546
[stutters] It feels like…

729
00:43:10,629 --> 00:43:12,631
You seem so strong, Victoria.
[chuckles]

730
00:43:14,425 --> 00:43:15,676
[ominous music plays]

731
00:43:15,759 --> 00:43:16,969
Is that a beard?

732
00:43:17,928 --> 00:43:19,555
And do I have red hair?

733
00:43:20,556 --> 00:43:23,183
-Goodbye, Dick!
-[screaming] Why can’t I move?

734
00:43:23,267 --> 00:43:24,643
[clamoring]

735
00:43:24,727 --> 00:43:26,437
Wait up, comrades!

736
00:43:27,146 --> 00:43:28,606
The chicken ass is mine.

737
00:43:28,689 --> 00:43:31,525
-[man] I'll take the butt part.
-Okay!

738
00:43:31,609 --> 00:43:33,527
-[gasping]
-Good luck!

739
00:43:35,654 --> 00:43:37,740
[breathing heavily]

740
00:43:40,743 --> 00:43:44,622
Beny, you’re awake! [groaning]

741
00:43:45,247 --> 00:43:46,457
Get ready!

742
00:43:46,540 --> 00:43:48,709
We might get reprimanded again.

743
00:43:48,792 --> 00:43:49,668
Beny?

744
00:43:51,211 --> 00:43:52,296
Who are you?

745
00:43:53,672 --> 00:43:57,134
Rodolfo, Beny, get ready.
You are next. Hurry up.

746
00:43:58,469 --> 00:44:01,388
[chuckles] Let's go, sleepyhead.

747
00:44:02,890 --> 00:44:04,975
We will be reprimanded again. You'll see.

748
00:44:06,560 --> 00:44:07,936
-Are you ready?
-Huh?

749
00:44:09,313 --> 00:44:10,481
Hurry up!

750
00:44:10,564 --> 00:44:14,068
Let’s give a round of applause!

751
00:44:14,151 --> 00:44:18,072
We had great performers tonight!

752
00:44:18,864 --> 00:44:22,117
But here's what
we've all been waiting for.

753
00:44:22,618 --> 00:44:25,537
The team-up of Rodolfo and…

754
00:44:26,997 --> 00:44:28,332
What's his name again?

755
00:44:28,415 --> 00:44:30,042
-[man] Beny!
-Huh? Jenny?

756
00:44:30,542 --> 00:44:32,252
-Beny
-Oh, Beny.

757
00:44:32,920 --> 00:44:36,882
The team-up of Rodolfo and Jenny!

758
00:44:36,965 --> 00:44:38,759
Round of applause!

759
00:44:38,842 --> 00:44:39,927
[claps]

760
00:44:40,886 --> 00:44:41,762
[Rodulfo exhales]

761
00:44:46,100 --> 00:44:47,518
[mumbling]

762
00:44:48,102 --> 00:44:48,936
Hey!

763
00:44:49,728 --> 00:44:51,522
[piano playing]

764
00:44:56,360 --> 00:44:58,237
Hey. Dance!

765
00:44:58,904 --> 00:45:00,614
-Huh?
-Dance.

766
00:45:00,698 --> 00:45:01,782
Dance?

767
00:45:01,865 --> 00:45:03,409
Dance. There are so many people.

768
00:45:04,868 --> 00:45:06,620
Dance? What kind of dance?

769
00:45:06,703 --> 00:45:07,996
Like this. Tap dance.

770
00:45:08,080 --> 00:45:11,166
Tap dance? That's a dance?
It's like removing poop from your shoes.

771
00:45:11,792 --> 00:45:13,627
This is what you call tap dance.

772
00:45:13,711 --> 00:45:14,628
Come on.

773
00:45:14,712 --> 00:45:16,588
-Okay.
-Game!

774
00:45:26,473 --> 00:45:29,935
[man snoring]

775
00:45:30,018 --> 00:45:31,812
-What kind of dance is that?
-Huh?

776
00:45:31,895 --> 00:45:32,896
Tap dance.

777
00:45:32,980 --> 00:45:34,148
Tap dance revolution.

778
00:45:37,651 --> 00:45:40,654
-[man 1 sighs]
-[man 2 whistles]

779
00:45:40,738 --> 00:45:42,656
[Rodulfo chuckles]

780
00:45:42,740 --> 00:45:45,784
[girl screaming]

781
00:45:45,868 --> 00:45:48,787
-[girl] When are you visiting us?
-[Rodulfo] It's up to you.

782
00:45:48,871 --> 00:45:50,622
Later, if you want?

783
00:45:50,706 --> 00:45:53,208
-Later? Okay!
-[moans softly]

784
00:45:53,667 --> 00:45:56,545
[gasps] He looks like Rizal!

785
00:45:59,047 --> 00:46:00,799
Bring him with you.

786
00:46:02,259 --> 00:46:03,260
[chuckles]

787
00:46:03,343 --> 00:46:05,429
[gasping]

788
00:46:05,512 --> 00:46:07,765
Okay, go ahead and we will follow.

789
00:46:07,848 --> 00:46:09,141
