Roberto?

1045
01:00:51,105 --> 01:00:53,441
What are you up to again this time?

1046
01:00:55,401 --> 01:00:57,362
What foolishness
are you planning to do

1047
01:00:57,445 --> 01:01:00,198
to save this man, Victorina?

1048
01:01:00,281 --> 01:01:02,408
I will do everything for him.

1049
01:01:02,492 --> 01:01:04,869
That's why, release him
and take me instead.

1050
01:01:04,952 --> 01:01:08,081
Roberto, you really are
the pain in my ass!

1051
01:01:08,164 --> 01:01:10,375
It’s me that you want. Deal with me.

1052
01:01:10,458 --> 01:01:12,001
The General made his decision,

1053
01:01:12,543 --> 01:01:13,586
and his decision is…

1054
01:01:14,337 --> 01:01:15,213
death!

1055
01:01:15,296 --> 01:01:17,632
-[breathes deeply]
-[gunshot]

1056
01:01:17,715 --> 01:01:18,925
[Benedict whimpers]

1057
01:01:20,426 --> 01:01:22,136
[dramatic music plays]

1058
01:01:22,220 --> 01:01:23,221
Victorina?

1059
01:01:25,306 --> 01:01:26,182
Victorina!

1060
01:01:28,101 --> 01:01:29,394
Victorina!

1061
01:01:29,477 --> 01:01:30,687
Victorina!

1062
01:01:34,982 --> 01:01:37,944
[heart beating]

1063
01:01:39,028 --> 01:01:40,613
[gasping]

1064
01:01:41,447 --> 01:01:43,700
Sir Saro! I need to go back.

1065
01:01:43,783 --> 01:01:46,285
Please give me a Wishkey.
I need to save my love.

1066
01:01:46,369 --> 01:01:48,413
What happened will never be changed.

1067
01:01:48,955 --> 01:01:50,915
You won’t be able to change her fate.

1068
01:01:50,998 --> 01:01:52,458
You don't understand!

1069
01:01:52,542 --> 01:01:54,293
I need to save Victoria!

1070
01:01:55,503 --> 01:01:56,671
Wait, okay?

1071
01:02:05,096 --> 01:02:06,055
I said wait.

1072
01:02:21,112 --> 01:02:22,530
-[breathing heavily]
-Here.

1073
01:02:32,749 --> 01:02:36,127
♪ <i>Ask me</i>
<i>Ask me</i> ♪

1074
01:02:36,627 --> 01:02:38,838
♪ <i>Who I love </i>♪

1075
01:02:39,964 --> 01:02:43,009
-Miss, one more beer, please.
-[song continues in background]

1076
01:02:43,092 --> 01:02:44,469
Okay.

1077
01:02:44,552 --> 01:02:45,887
[gasps]

1078
01:02:47,096 --> 01:02:49,724
Hey, best friend.
You bastard! You betrayed me!

1079
01:02:49,807 --> 01:02:51,559
Hey! Best friend, calm down.

1080
01:02:51,642 --> 01:02:53,102
Best friend. You’re drunk.

1081
01:02:53,603 --> 01:02:56,397
You slept in the middle of my stories.

1082
01:02:56,481 --> 01:02:57,940
There’s still so much beer.

1083
01:02:58,941 --> 01:03:00,860
-[glass clinking]
-What did you say?

1084
01:03:01,527 --> 01:03:02,612
We are best friends?

1085
01:03:02,695 --> 01:03:04,614
Yes, we are best friends.

1086
01:03:05,573 --> 01:03:08,117
You forgot because you drank too much.

1087
01:03:08,201 --> 01:03:09,785
Wait, I'll order more.

1088
01:03:12,330 --> 01:03:13,247
Excuse me.

1089
01:03:19,712 --> 01:03:20,546
[sighs]

1090
01:03:21,214 --> 01:03:24,300
Sorry about that, bestie.

1091
01:03:24,801 --> 01:03:26,219
Maybe I was just drunk.

1092
01:03:27,136 --> 01:03:29,680
-Cheers!
-[man] Cheers!

1093
01:03:30,640 --> 01:03:31,933
You're so amazing!

1094
01:03:32,642 --> 01:03:33,976
What is that?

1095
01:03:34,560 --> 01:03:36,979
-I mean, the singer, amazing.
-[clapping]

1096
01:03:37,980 --> 01:03:39,023
You're right.

1097
01:03:41,192 --> 01:03:42,026
Hey!

1098
01:03:42,527 --> 01:03:44,570
-Hypebeast.
-Hypebeast?

1099
01:03:45,112 --> 01:03:47,156
What do you mean?

1100
01:03:47,240 --> 01:03:48,449
What I mean is,

1101
01:03:48,533 --> 01:03:50,493
hype, peace, man!

1102
01:03:50,576 --> 01:03:51,661
[laughing]

1103
01:03:51,744 --> 01:03:54,497
I knew I would find you there.

1104
01:03:55,665 --> 01:03:57,625
I know you so well.

1105
01:03:58,543 --> 01:03:59,961
What is bothering you?

1106
01:04:00,711 --> 01:04:01,546
Me?

1107
01:04:04,882 --> 01:04:05,967
That’s all right.

1108
01:04:06,926 --> 01:04:07,969
I’m on your side.

1109
01:04:08,594 --> 01:04:12,598
Because, if not for you,
I wouldn't get a girlfriend.

1110
01:04:16,310 --> 01:04:17,436
You have a girlfriend?

1111
01:04:18,104 --> 01:04:19,146
[coughing]

1112
01:04:19,689 --> 01:04:21,983
Dude, what have you been drinking?

1113
01:04:22,066 --> 01:04:24,026
Yes, I have.

1114
01:04:25,152 --> 01:04:26,487
Come on. Let's go inside.

1115
01:04:27,029 --> 01:04:28,614
Why did you bring him here?

1116
01:04:29,824 --> 01:04:31,075
[in English] Sorry.

1117
01:04:31,158 --> 01:04:33,286
He got so drunk. That's why I brought him.

1118
01:04:33,953 --> 01:04:36,622
You should have let him
crawl home by himself.

1119
01:04:37,123 --> 01:04:39,125
I can't do that to him, sweetheart.

1120
01:04:40,001 --> 01:04:40,877
[retching]

1121
01:04:41,836 --> 01:04:42,837
You’re sweethearts?

1122
01:04:45,464 --> 01:04:49,635
Dude, go inside and have some coffee
so you can sober up.

1123
01:04:49,719 --> 01:04:50,678
But…

1124
01:04:50,761 --> 01:04:53,264
Careful, you drank too much.

1125
01:04:53,806 --> 01:04:54,849
[sighs]

1126
01:04:56,392 --> 01:04:58,978
[light music playing]

1127
01:05:10,031 --> 01:05:11,449
Do you want some water?

1128
01:05:12,033 --> 01:05:15,077
-Yes.
-Wait a minute. Wait a minute.

1129
01:05:37,767 --> 01:05:40,937
Uh… Victoria, can we talk?

1130
01:05:42,188 --> 01:05:43,272
Who’s Victoria?

1131
01:05:44,565 --> 01:05:46,108
Vicky! Water!

1132
01:05:48,152 --> 01:05:50,655
Victoria, the girl from the bar.
She looks just like you.

1133
01:05:51,906 --> 01:05:52,740
Vicky.

1134
01:05:53,407 --> 01:05:54,992
What have I done to you?

1135
01:05:55,576 --> 01:05:57,078
You don't know, Ben?

1136
01:05:58,287 --> 01:06:00,873
If I knew, I wouldn't be asking you now.

1137
01:06:00,957 --> 01:06:04,085
You know what? If you don't know,
then don't bother asking.

1138
01:06:04,168 --> 01:06:05,169
Know what?

1139
01:06:05,252 --> 01:06:08,631
The thing you said that you don't know!
[sigh]

1140
01:06:08,714 --> 01:06:11,300
[Benedict] Why don't you just tell me
what you know,

1141
01:06:11,884 --> 01:06:13,427
so that I will know it also?

1142
01:06:13,970 --> 01:06:14,887
Right?

1143
01:06:17,098 --> 01:06:20,226
I don't care if you don’t know
what I know.

1144
01:06:22,436 --> 01:06:23,562
But Vicky…

1145
01:06:32,863 --> 01:06:33,990
I put salt, didn’t I?

1146
01:06:34,991 --> 01:06:36,534
Yes, I like my coffee salty.

1147
01:06:39,870 --> 01:06:40,955
Tastes like the sea!

1148
01:06:42,540 --> 01:06:44,792
[man] Dude, I have a favor
to ask from you.

1149
01:06:44,875 --> 01:06:46,752
[man] You're my best friend, right?

1150
01:06:46,836 --> 01:06:48,004
What is it?

1151
01:06:49,213 --> 01:06:52,133
-[man] Help me take Vicky away.
-[clacking]

1152
01:06:53,634 --> 01:06:55,970
What? You're eloping with Vicky?

1153
01:06:56,804 --> 01:06:57,805
Yes!

1154
01:06:57,888 --> 01:07:02,268
Dude, you know that her parents
disapprove of me.

1155
01:07:03,310 --> 01:07:06,272
[sighs] And we planned this
a long time ago.

1156
01:07:07,606 --> 01:07:09,608
But I cannot do it alone.

1157
01:07:09,692 --> 01:07:12,445
That's why I need your help.

1158
01:07:12,987 --> 01:07:15,406
[sighs] But…

1159
01:07:16,031 --> 01:07:17,992
Dude, not that way.

1160
01:07:18,993 --> 01:07:20,494
Eloping is a different matter.

1161
01:07:21,787 --> 01:07:22,747
Dude.

1162
01:07:23,706 --> 01:07:25,458
Are you going to bail on me now?

1163
01:07:25,541 --> 01:07:28,419
You even agreed on the previous favor
I asked of you.

1164
01:07:29,211 --> 01:07:30,337
What previous favor?

1165
01:07:30,421 --> 01:07:31,672
To date Vicky.

1166
01:07:31,756 --> 01:07:33,424
[man] When you broke up with her.

1167
01:07:34,508 --> 01:07:36,469
-I said that?
-Yes.

1168
01:07:37,011 --> 01:07:39,221
You told me you don't like her anymore.

1169
01:07:39,305 --> 01:07:42,391
And remember, you owe me a lot as well.

1170
01:07:43,976 --> 01:07:46,479
[ball clacking]

1171
01:07:46,562 --> 01:07:48,773
I'm very sorry, friends.

1172
01:07:53,611 --> 01:07:55,946
-[tense music playing]
-Did you who shoot this?

1173
01:07:56,030 --> 01:07:58,282
[man] We've been trying to do that
for three hours,

1174
01:07:58,365 --> 01:08:01,243
and you just shoot it that easily?
And from the other table?

1175
01:08:01,744 --> 01:08:04,330
But Pacquito, he is good.

1176
01:08:06,540 --> 01:08:07,583
Stop it, Rez!

1177
01:08:11,462 --> 01:08:14,340
Do you want me to crush this
in front of you? Huh?

1178
01:08:16,634 --> 01:08:18,511
Bomber. Do it.

1179
01:08:21,889 --> 01:08:23,933
[grunting]

1180
01:08:24,016 --> 01:08:24,975
Let me do it.

1181
01:08:26,685 --> 01:08:27,937
[squeaking]

1182
01:08:29,271 --> 01:08:30,481
It's Bata! It's Bata!

1183
01:08:30,564 --> 01:08:31,690
Bata?

1184
01:08:31,774 --> 01:08:35,027
-[crowd cheering]
-[Benedict] Right. It's really Bata.

1185
01:08:35,111 --> 01:08:36,237
Who’s Bata?

1186
01:08:36,320 --> 01:08:38,572
Ben, I'll go ahead. I need to see Vicky.

1187
01:08:38,656 --> 01:08:41,283
-All right!
-[man] Bata!

1188
01:08:41,367 --> 01:08:42,952
[Benedict] He has a mustache?

1189
01:08:43,035 --> 01:08:44,078
Bata?

1190
01:08:56,757 --> 01:08:59,969
[panting]

1191
01:09:00,928 --> 01:09:02,721
Vicky! Vicky!

1192
01:09:02,805 --> 01:09:04,849
-[girl]What is that!
-Oh my!

1193
01:09:04,932 --> 01:09:07,017
Grandma, is Vicky around?

1194
01:09:09,103 --> 01:09:10,437
Kristina!

1195
01:09:11,021 --> 01:09:13,440
Why are you wearing my clothes again?

1196
01:09:13,524 --> 01:09:15,317
I just tried it on. What’s wrong?

1197
01:09:15,401 --> 01:09:18,737
It looks good on me anyway.
You don't want to lend me your clothes.

1198
01:09:18,821 --> 01:09:20,948
I will just wash them or buy you new ones!

1199
01:09:21,031 --> 01:09:23,450
Vicky, can we talk?

1200
01:09:23,534 --> 01:09:26,245
What for? We are done!

1201
01:09:26,829 --> 01:09:30,541
-Bert is here. Get out!
-You need to hear me out.

1202
01:09:30,624 --> 01:09:32,710
-[Benedict] Please hear me out.
-Go out!

1203
01:09:32,793 --> 01:09:34,003
Get out of here!

1204
01:09:34,837 --> 01:09:38,007
Ouch! I want to explain everything to you.

1205
01:09:39,466 --> 01:09:42,303
Please forget about
whatever I did wrong before.

1206
01:09:42,386 --> 01:09:45,890
Which one?
Neglecting me as your girlfriend?

1207
01:09:45,973 --> 01:09:47,474
[rattling]

1208
01:09:47,558 --> 01:09:48,726
[grunts]

1209
01:09:49,435 --> 01:09:51,187
I can never do that to you.

1210
01:09:52,980 --> 01:09:53,856
I mean, Vicky!

1211
01:09:53,939 --> 01:09:56,859
See, you're still thinking
about the girl in the bar.

1212
01:09:56,942 --> 01:09:59,278
You did it when we were still together.

1213
01:09:59,361 --> 01:10:03,073
You don't have time for me
or for our relationship.

1214
01:10:03,157 --> 01:10:06,869
You only care about yourself.
So please get out of here.

1215
01:10:06,952 --> 01:10:08,037
[rattling]

1216
01:10:08,621 --> 01:10:09,872
[grunting]

1217
01:10:10,706 --> 01:10:11,707
But Vicky,

1218
01:10:12,541 --> 01:10:13,584
please forgive me.

1219
01:10:14,335 --> 01:10:15,502
Let me explain.

1220
01:10:16,462 --> 01:10:18,005
Everything is clear to me.

1221
01:10:18,714 --> 01:10:21,091
Because of what you did, I met Bert.

1222
01:10:21,175 --> 01:10:25,095
He showed me how to love and be loved.

1223
01:10:26,513 --> 01:10:28,515
[banging]

1224
01:10:33,604 --> 01:10:36,732
[sad music playing]

1225
01:10:40,319 --> 01:10:42,571
[tense music playing]

1226
01:10:44,490 --> 01:10:46,992
-[gasping]
-[woman] Hey! What are you doing there?

1227
01:10:47,076 --> 01:10:48,369
[screaming]

1228
01:10:48,452 --> 01:10:49,662
Ouch!

1229
01:10:50,704 --> 01:10:52,373
Are you okay?

1230
01:10:53,415 --> 01:10:55,918
[gasping]

1231
01:10:56,502 --> 01:10:57,711
-Mom?
-[gasps]

1232
01:10:58,254 --> 01:11:00,839
I'm not your mom.
I don't have a husband and kids.

1233
01:11:00,923 --> 01:11:03,050
[grunting]

1234
01:11:03,133 --> 01:11:05,594
You're overreacting.
You won’t die jumping from there.

1235
01:11:05,678 --> 01:11:07,096
That’s too low!

1236
01:11:07,179 --> 01:11:10,599
You should be thankful
that I have not put away my laundry.

1237
01:11:11,475 --> 01:11:15,145
-[flicking lighter]
-[Benedict grunting]

1238
01:11:15,229 --> 01:11:17,856
Hey! Don't jump.

1239
01:11:18,399 --> 01:11:21,068
I'm not jumping. I'm just stretching.

1240
01:11:21,151 --> 01:11:22,945
My body aches because of my fall.

1241
01:11:24,363 --> 01:11:26,991
You know what?
You really have a big problem.

1242
01:11:27,074 --> 01:11:28,200
Bigger than you think.

1243
01:11:29,493 --> 01:11:32,371
It's because the person I love
went with someone else.

1244
01:11:32,454 --> 01:11:34,915
But why?

1245
01:11:35,624 --> 01:11:40,379
I don't know. I've done everything
I could, but it still happened.

1246
01:11:41,005 --> 01:11:42,298
Are you sure?

1247
01:11:42,381 --> 01:11:43,882
You know how she feels?

1248
01:11:43,966 --> 01:11:46,260
We women,
what we expect from the person we love

1249
01:11:46,343 --> 01:11:48,595
is that they know how we feel
even without talking.

1250
01:11:48,679 --> 01:11:49,972
That they understand us.

1251
01:11:50,055 --> 01:11:51,181
Wait up.

1252
01:11:51,807 --> 01:11:54,226
I'm the one who has a problem.
Why are you upset?

1253
01:11:54,309 --> 01:11:57,980
You remind me of my love. Dominador.

1254
01:11:58,647 --> 01:12:00,607
Why? What happened between you and Dad?

1255
01:12:00,691 --> 01:12:02,484
I mean with the person you love.

1256
01:12:03,235 --> 01:12:05,904
My parents don't want him for me.

1257
01:12:05,988 --> 01:12:07,906
They want me to work abroad.

1258
01:12:08,574 --> 01:12:09,783
How will I be born?

1259
01:12:10,326 --> 01:12:14,413
When you love someone,
shouldn't you fight for him?

1260
01:12:15,080 --> 01:12:18,334
You still have time.
Do everything you can.

1261
01:12:21,378 --> 01:12:23,088
It’s a beautiful thing you said.

1262
01:12:27,926 --> 01:12:30,012
Wait. What are you doing?

1263
01:12:30,721 --> 01:12:33,265
It’s your fault. I remembered
my Dominador,

1264
01:12:33,349 --> 01:12:35,100
and what you said was so beautiful.

1265
01:12:35,768 --> 01:12:37,436
You know what? You're right.

1266
01:12:37,519 --> 01:12:41,273
I still have time. I'll tell Mama and Papa
that I love Dominador very much.

1267
01:12:41,357 --> 01:12:43,734
And I will do everything
for us not to separate.

1268
01:12:45,110 --> 01:12:46,862
What you said was nice.

1269
01:12:47,446 --> 01:12:50,324
That's what I'm going to do with Vicky.
I still have time.

1270
01:12:50,866 --> 01:12:51,909
You're amazing, Mom!

1271
01:12:51,992 --> 01:12:54,078
I'm not your mom!

1272
01:12:54,161 --> 01:12:55,788
Virginia is my name.

1273
01:12:55,871 --> 01:12:58,457
Virginia, I am Benedict.

1274
01:12:59,708 --> 01:13:00,876
Benedict.

1275
01:13:01,460 --> 01:13:02,461
Thank you.

1276
01:13:06,340 --> 01:13:07,257
Bye.

1277
01:13:26,235 --> 01:13:27,486
Where is Bert?

1278
01:13:28,612 --> 01:13:29,863
Vicky, forget about Bert.

1279
01:13:30,531 --> 01:13:32,241
Vicky, I still love you.

1280
01:13:32,324 --> 01:13:34,827
Come with me and I’ll give you everything.

1281
01:13:35,744 --> 01:13:39,206
-I'll do everything you want.
-I thought you already understood me?

1282
01:13:40,499 --> 01:13:41,542
Vicky,

1283
01:13:42,960 --> 01:13:44,586
give me a second chance.

1284
01:13:45,379 --> 01:13:46,713
Like what John Lloyd once said,

1285
01:13:48,006 --> 01:13:50,843
"Give me one more chance
to show you how much I love you."

1286
01:13:51,593 --> 01:13:54,429
Vicky, I can't live without you,
no matter when.

1287
01:13:54,513 --> 01:13:56,098
Who is John Lloyd?

1288
01:13:57,724 --> 01:13:59,852
John Lloyd, the poet.

1289
01:13:59,935 --> 01:14:02,813
Ben! I don't love you anymore.

1290
01:14:02,896 --> 01:14:06,191
Do you understand?
I don't love you anymore!

1291
01:14:06,692 --> 01:14:09,403
-I don't love you!
-[slaps]

1292
01:14:13,198 --> 01:14:14,074
[banging]

1293
01:14:15,742 --> 01:14:17,911
[gate opening]

1294
01:14:19,496 --> 01:14:21,748
[heart beating heavily]

1295
01:14:23,542 --> 01:14:25,002
Want to take me instead?

1296
01:14:25,586 --> 01:14:26,670
[gasps]

1297
01:14:26,753 --> 01:14:28,547
No. I'll just get the bag.

1298
01:14:29,590 --> 01:14:30,966
[gasping]

1299
01:14:32,843 --> 01:14:34,011
Do you still want more?

1300
01:14:37,222 --> 01:14:38,182
No, thanks.

1301
01:14:39,808 --> 01:14:41,310
I have no reason to go back.

1302
01:14:43,103 --> 01:14:44,730
I don't need your Wishkey!

1303
01:14:45,981 --> 01:14:47,357
[glasses shattering]

1304
01:14:49,485 --> 01:14:50,694
[glasses shattering]

1305
01:14:51,570 --> 01:14:53,363
[gasps]

1306
01:14:59,536 --> 01:15:02,456
[melancholic music playing]

1307
01:15:07,044 --> 01:15:10,005
[clock ringing]

1308
01:15:22,351 --> 01:15:24,061
[knocking]

1309
01:15:25,062 --> 01:15:26,355
Brother?

1310
01:15:27,147 --> 01:15:28,232
[Bela] Are you okay?

1311
01:15:29,191 --> 01:15:30,776
-[knocking]
-Brother?

1312
01:15:34,571 --> 01:15:35,572
I'm okay.

1313
01:15:37,783 --> 01:15:39,868
-[Bela] You're not okay.
-I'm okay.

1314
01:15:40,619 --> 01:15:41,620
Mm?

1315
01:15:45,832 --> 01:15:48,085
Yeah. Yeah.

1316
01:15:48,710 --> 01:15:50,337
There. Do you want to eat now?

1317
01:15:51,630 --> 01:15:53,465
I said I don't want to eat!

1318
01:15:55,008 --> 01:15:56,301
So arrogant!

1319
01:15:58,845 --> 01:16:03,392
Then don't! I'm hungry!
I’ll eat if you don’t.

1320
01:16:10,274 --> 01:16:11,900
Son! Son! Come on! Try it!

1321
01:16:11,984 --> 01:16:14,069
-I can't beat your sister.
-Come on!

1322
01:16:14,778 --> 01:16:16,238
Dad, I'm not in the mood.

1323
01:16:31,295 --> 01:16:33,880
[sobbing]

1324
01:16:43,557 --> 01:16:44,641
Dad.

1325
01:16:45,892 --> 01:16:47,603
If only I knew that

1326
01:16:47,686 --> 01:16:49,646
I would see Mom
for the last time at the airport,

1327
01:16:51,064 --> 01:16:52,733
I wish I didn't let her go.

1328
01:16:54,693 --> 01:16:55,611
Son.

1329
01:16:58,739 --> 01:17:04,244
That's your mother's destiny.

1330
01:17:07,247 --> 01:17:09,625
It happened.
We cannot do anything about it anymore.

1331
01:17:10,834 --> 01:17:15,339
Even if I blame myself
for not stopping her.

1332
01:17:16,465 --> 01:17:17,466
That's it.

1333
01:17:20,802 --> 01:17:21,845
Why, Dad?

1334
01:17:24,348 --> 01:17:27,684
Son, if only I can turn back time--

1335
01:17:27,768 --> 01:17:30,270
[Bela] Dad, the car is here.

1336
01:17:31,438 --> 01:17:33,440
Are you sure you're not coming?

1337
01:17:33,523 --> 01:17:35,275
You go ahead.

1338
01:17:36,026 --> 01:17:37,027
Yes, take care.

1339
01:17:38,403 --> 01:17:40,322
You might see ghosts here.

1340
01:17:40,405 --> 01:17:42,574
[sigh] You take care.

1341
01:17:45,035 --> 01:17:47,287
[Bela] Dad, why did you have to scare him?

1342
01:17:50,666 --> 01:17:51,625
Mom.

1343
01:17:52,709 --> 01:17:54,336
What do I still need to correct?

1344
01:17:55,670 --> 01:17:57,047
I already did everything.

1345
01:18:00,550 --> 01:18:02,094
-Sir, aren’t you going home?
-[gasps]

1346
01:18:03,261 --> 01:18:04,638
I thought you were a ghost.

1347
01:18:06,556 --> 01:18:07,391
I am.

1348
01:18:07,474 --> 01:18:08,975
[ominous music]

1349
01:18:10,560 --> 01:18:12,145
Aren’t you too early?

1350
01:18:12,229 --> 01:18:13,855
Aren’t you from the night shift?

1351
01:18:15,941 --> 01:18:17,317
[breathing heavily]

1352
01:18:25,158 --> 01:18:27,327
[voice whispering] Turning Point.

1353
01:18:28,495 --> 01:18:30,288
[suspenseful music]

1354
01:18:34,710 --> 01:18:35,627
Sir Saro.

1355
01:18:36,586 --> 01:18:37,462
Sir Saro.

1356
01:18:38,213 --> 01:18:39,297
Yes?

1357
01:18:41,591 --> 01:18:42,467
What?

1358
01:18:44,177 --> 01:18:45,637
I thought you're done.

1359
01:18:45,721 --> 01:18:46,930
That's what I thought.

1360
01:18:49,266 --> 01:18:51,017
Do you want to go back to the past?

1361
01:18:51,101 --> 01:18:52,102
Yes!

1362
01:18:53,770 --> 01:18:54,813
Are you sure?

1363
01:18:55,397 --> 01:18:57,858
But now, I will make sure
I will do it right.

1364
01:19:01,236 --> 01:19:03,155
-Are you really sure?
-I'm really sure!

1365
01:19:18,795 --> 01:19:19,755
Cheers?

1366
01:19:21,339 --> 01:19:22,507
[sighs deeply]

1367
01:19:31,475 --> 01:19:35,228
Why did you eat all the chocolates?
Look at you! You're a mess!

1368
01:19:35,729 --> 01:19:37,939
You know that your salary is not enough.

1369
01:19:38,023 --> 01:19:40,108
Benedict is going to grade 4.

1370
01:19:40,192 --> 01:19:42,027
Bela will soon go to school.

1371
01:19:42,110 --> 01:19:44,237
Hilda! Clean her up.

1372
01:19:44,321 --> 01:19:46,948
I'll get an extra job. Just don't leave.

1373
01:19:47,449 --> 01:19:49,451
I will not waste the opportunity.

1374
01:19:49,534 --> 01:19:51,286
It is only a six-month contract.

1375
01:19:51,369 --> 01:19:52,704
It’ll be quick.

1376
01:19:52,788 --> 01:19:54,206
What about our children?

1377
01:19:54,289 --> 01:19:58,210
I know that you'll take care of them.
This is for our family's sake.

1378
01:19:59,127 --> 01:20:02,005
Benedict, why are you still here?
You need to take a bath.

1379
01:20:02,714 --> 01:20:04,800
This TV is still on?

1380
01:20:08,136 --> 01:20:09,304
[gasps]

1381
01:20:16,603 --> 01:20:18,355
I went back to my childhood.

1382
01:20:26,112 --> 01:20:27,531
Ah! Still uncut!

1383
01:20:31,034 --> 01:20:32,118
Yes.

1384
01:20:32,994 --> 01:20:36,414
Help! Help! I'm stuck in the escalator!

1385
01:20:36,498 --> 01:20:40,961
I need to go.
Always obey your dad. Be good.

1386
01:20:41,044 --> 01:20:42,921
-Come on!
-Let's go now.

1387
01:20:43,004 --> 01:20:47,634
By the way, don't forget Bela's milk.

1388
01:20:47,717 --> 01:20:50,220
Let her sleep in the afternoon.

1389
01:20:50,303 --> 01:20:52,973
Her vitamins. I already put--

1390
01:20:53,056 --> 01:20:54,224
Mom!

1391
01:20:54,307 --> 01:20:57,269
[emotional music playing]

1392
01:20:57,352 --> 01:20:58,311
Son.

1393
01:20:59,020 --> 01:21:03,692
Son, don't be sad.
I'll be quick, and you won’t notice it.

1394
01:21:03,775 --> 01:21:05,986
[announcement, in English] <i>Last call!</i>

1395
01:21:06,069 --> 01:21:08,947
-[airport announcer speaking]
-Okay! Okay!

1396
01:21:17,497 --> 01:21:19,541
Ouch!

1397
01:21:20,417 --> 01:21:22,627
It hurts!

1398
01:21:22,711 --> 01:21:24,379
It hurts!

1399
01:21:24,462 --> 01:21:25,505
Wait!

1400
01:21:25,589 --> 01:21:27,173
Wait! I need to check my son.

1401
01:21:27,257 --> 01:21:28,425
I don't know.

1402
01:21:28,508 --> 01:21:29,509
Mom! It hurts!

1403
01:21:29,593 --> 01:21:31,386
What happened?

1404
01:21:31,469 --> 01:21:33,305
I need to go.

1405
01:21:33,388 --> 01:21:34,514
Come on!

1406
01:21:34,598 --> 01:21:35,682
It hurts!

1407
01:21:35,765 --> 01:21:39,519
Why are you having a stomachache?

1408
01:21:39,603 --> 01:21:41,062
It hurts!

1409
01:21:41,146 --> 01:21:46,902
An airplane crashed 300 kilometers
after it took off.

1410
01:21:46,985 --> 01:21:50,488
-<i>According to our sources,</i>
-Sir, can you turn up the volume?

1411
01:21:50,572 --> 01:21:55,035
-<i>it was supposed to fly to Hong Kong.</i>
-[Benedict] It hurts.

1412
01:21:55,118 --> 01:21:56,745
<i>According to reports,</i>

1413
01:21:56,828 --> 01:22:00,874
-<i>there were no survivors.</i>
-Oh my. That was my flight earlier.

1414
01:22:02,208 --> 01:22:04,044
Yay!

1415
01:22:05,754 --> 01:22:07,130
Eh? Why?

1416
01:22:09,507 --> 01:22:11,509
My stomach doesn't hurt anymore.

1417
01:22:12,177 --> 01:22:13,261
[mother sighs]

1418
01:22:22,687 --> 01:22:24,981
You're eating too much.

1419
01:22:26,024 --> 01:22:27,943
Are you sure your stomach is good now?

1420
01:22:28,026 --> 01:22:30,612
Yes, I'm now okay.

1421
01:22:32,280 --> 01:22:33,698
You eat too much.

1422
01:22:35,575 --> 01:22:37,535
-My mom will not leave anymore.
-My bag!

1423
01:22:37,619 --> 01:22:39,204
-My family is complete.
-[brakes squeal]

1424
01:22:39,287 --> 01:22:40,121
[crash]

1425
01:22:41,790 --> 01:22:43,500
[dramatic music playing]

1426
01:22:43,583 --> 01:22:44,834
[father] Virginia!

1427
01:22:46,002 --> 01:22:47,170
Virginia!

1428
01:22:49,547 --> 01:22:50,507
Son.

1429
01:22:51,216 --> 01:22:52,509
Son!

1430
01:22:52,592 --> 01:22:55,595
Son! Stay there. Don’t go closer.

1431
01:22:55,679 --> 01:22:57,097
Mom!

1432
01:22:58,723 --> 01:23:00,642
Stay there. Don’t go closer.

1433
01:23:00,725 --> 01:23:02,852
Virginia! Virginia!

1434
01:23:03,353 --> 01:23:04,354
My love.

1435
01:23:05,105 --> 01:23:06,606
Mom…

1436
01:23:08,692 --> 01:23:10,860
[heart beating heavily]

1437
01:23:22,998 --> 01:23:23,873
Mom?

1438
01:23:31,005 --> 01:23:32,882
[crying]

1439
01:23:35,885 --> 01:23:38,304
Why wasn't I able to stop my Mom's death?

1440
01:23:41,016 --> 01:23:41,933
Benedict.

1441
01:23:43,435 --> 01:23:44,811
In this journey,

1442
01:23:45,937 --> 01:23:47,188
it's a different story

1443
01:23:47,897 --> 01:23:49,441
when it comes to…

1444
01:23:51,276 --> 01:23:52,902
life and death.

1445
01:23:53,570 --> 01:23:56,948
The only thing permanent is…

1446
01:23:58,074 --> 01:24:01,411
the birth and death of a person.

1447
01:24:01,995 --> 01:24:03,663
What's the use of that Wishkey

1448
01:24:03,747 --> 01:24:05,623
if it can't change my fate?

1449
01:24:06,750 --> 01:24:07,625
[sighs]

1450
01:24:08,460 --> 01:24:10,170
The purpose of the Wishkey

1451
01:24:11,379 --> 01:24:13,548
is not to change what happened in the past

1452
01:24:15,175 --> 01:24:17,761
but rather for you to realize and change

1453
01:24:18,720 --> 01:24:21,890
what you should do in the present.

1454
01:24:23,016 --> 01:24:25,226
But how do you know about this?

1455
01:24:25,977 --> 01:24:26,936
Who are you?

1456
01:24:27,520 --> 01:24:29,939
Like you, I also made a mistake.

1457
01:24:31,733 --> 01:24:33,068
I also wanted to go back.

1458
01:24:35,195 --> 01:24:37,655
I abused it
because of my selfish intentions.

1459
01:24:38,573 --> 01:24:41,743
This is my punishment.

1460
01:24:41,826 --> 01:24:44,079
Listen to those who failed,

1461
01:24:44,996 --> 01:24:47,749
those who have been hurt many times,

1462
01:24:48,458 --> 01:24:49,459
so I can teach

1463
01:24:50,835 --> 01:24:53,463
the right things from my experience.

1464
01:24:59,803 --> 01:25:00,845
Last shot?

1465
01:25:09,395 --> 01:25:10,563
-Cheers?
-Table.

1466
01:25:17,612 --> 01:25:19,697
[freeze]

1467
01:25:22,075 --> 01:25:23,284
[sighs]

1468
01:25:29,374 --> 01:25:32,210
[Victoria] Babe, it is not my birthday.

1469
01:25:34,129 --> 01:25:35,880
It is also not our anniversary.

1470
01:25:36,840 --> 01:25:37,799
What's this for?

1471
01:25:38,508 --> 01:25:40,718
I know there's something
you want to tell me.

1472
01:25:42,137 --> 01:25:43,012
But,

1473
01:25:43,888 --> 01:25:45,348
is it okay if I go first?

1474
01:25:46,057 --> 01:25:48,309
You know what I want to tell you?

1475
01:25:48,893 --> 01:25:49,811
You want

1476
01:25:51,146 --> 01:25:52,856
to break up with me, right?

1477
01:25:54,315 --> 01:25:55,358
[sighs deeply]

1478
01:25:56,776 --> 01:25:58,778
Wait, babe, they’ll sing.

1479
01:25:58,862 --> 01:26:01,823
[guitar playing]

1480
01:26:05,201 --> 01:26:07,328
Our relationship is getting toxic.

1481
01:26:09,038 --> 01:26:10,874
You want me to obey you always.

1482
01:26:12,000 --> 01:26:14,961
-This restaurant--
-Because

1483
01:26:15,670 --> 01:26:17,297
you're allergic to seafood.

1484
01:26:18,423 --> 01:26:19,507
You know what, babe?

1485
01:26:20,300 --> 01:26:22,093
You're right.

1486
01:26:22,844 --> 01:26:24,679
No matter what your decision is,

1487
01:26:26,639 --> 01:26:27,891
I will understand.

1488
01:26:30,351 --> 01:26:33,521
Because I'm not the old Benedict
that will control your life.

1489
01:26:37,358 --> 01:26:39,360
I will give you freedom.

1490
01:26:41,321 --> 01:26:44,991
Freedom to decide for yourself
and for your family.

1491
01:26:47,577 --> 01:26:48,536
No matter

1492
01:26:50,663 --> 01:26:52,498
how many years will pass by…

1493
01:26:55,335 --> 01:26:58,838
my love for you will never change.

1494
01:27:01,090 --> 01:27:02,508
I'm sorry, Benedict.

1495
01:27:06,429 --> 01:27:07,388
[sighs]

1496
01:27:08,723 --> 01:27:11,559
[in English] It's okay. I understand.

1497
01:27:24,239 --> 01:27:26,824
[delicate music playing]

1498
01:27:28,910 --> 01:27:34,082
[heart beating heavily]

1499
01:27:55,061 --> 01:27:58,106
[dramatic music playing]

1500
01:28:03,778 --> 01:28:06,906
[man] Hey, stop it, bro…

1501
01:28:07,949 --> 01:28:09,200
[man] Listen to me.

1502
01:28:10,326 --> 01:28:12,036
[man] Our friends left us already.

1503
01:28:13,288 --> 01:28:14,372
Hey, bro…

1504
01:28:14,455 --> 01:28:17,458
-[thunder rumbling]
-[suspenseful music playing]

1505
01:28:19,627 --> 01:28:21,754
[voice whispering] Turning Point.

1506
01:28:25,133 --> 01:28:26,676
[man] We can go home now.

1507
01:28:29,387 --> 01:28:30,888
[thunder rumbling]

1508
01:28:30,972 --> 01:28:32,515
[man] Ouch!

1509
01:28:45,987 --> 01:28:48,531
[delicate music playing]

1510
01:28:52,035 --> 01:28:53,828
[caller] <i>Papa Tak, I'm Jane.</i>

1511
01:28:53,911 --> 01:28:55,121
Hello, Jane.

1512
01:28:55,204 --> 01:28:58,082
[caller] <i>I just wanna ask</i>
<i>what I should do with my ex</i>

1513
01:28:58,166 --> 01:29:00,710
<i>because I've realized</i>
<i>that I still love him.</i>

1514
01:29:00,793 --> 01:29:03,212
[Benedict] <i>Jane, it is very simple.</i>

1515
01:29:03,296 --> 01:29:05,798
<i>If you realized that you still love him,</i>

1516
01:29:05,882 --> 01:29:08,676
<i>you need to talk to him.</i>

1517
01:29:09,761 --> 01:29:11,429
<i>Tell him that</i>

1518
01:29:13,139 --> 01:29:14,265
<i>you still love him.</i>

1519
01:29:15,141 --> 01:29:17,018
<i>You should be true to yourself.</i>

1520
01:29:17,101 --> 01:29:19,270
[caller] <i>What if</i>
<i>he doesn't love me anymore?</i>

1521
01:29:19,771 --> 01:29:22,565
[Benedict]
<i>Jane, how can we know the answer</i>

1522
01:29:23,358 --> 01:29:24,942
<i>if you don't talk to him?</i>

1523
01:29:25,026 --> 01:29:26,152
<i>You know what, Jane?</i>

1524
01:29:27,070 --> 01:29:29,489
<i>Communication is very important</i>
<i>in a relationship</i>

1525
01:29:30,782 --> 01:29:34,535
<i>to know that you still love each other.</i>

1526
01:29:35,119 --> 01:29:38,498
<i>Jane, try to talk to him.</i>

1527
01:29:39,415 --> 01:29:41,542
<i>Tell him that you</i>
<i>can't afford to lose him.</i>

1528
01:29:43,127 --> 01:29:45,880
[voice cracking]
Tell him that you still love him.

1529
01:29:48,758 --> 01:29:50,593
Do you understand me, Jane?

1530
01:29:50,676 --> 01:29:53,137
[caller] <i>Yes, Papa Tak. Thank you.</i>

1531
01:30:04,774 --> 01:30:06,776
[delicate music playing]

1532
01:30:19,247 --> 01:30:20,498
We haven't been paid yet.

1533
01:30:21,207 --> 01:30:24,335
Perhaps someone can pay in the meantime.

1534
01:30:34,804 --> 01:30:36,305
[gentle piano music playing]

1535
01:30:36,389 --> 01:30:38,808
[Hugot Tina] Look, it's her.
They finally meet.

1536
01:30:44,230 --> 01:30:45,398
You're late.

1537
01:30:47,650 --> 01:30:50,862
Sorry, we came from work, then--

1538
01:30:53,573 --> 01:30:54,490
Wait.

1539
01:30:55,616 --> 01:30:57,618
Did we have plans for tonight?

1540
01:30:58,161 --> 01:31:00,455
Ah, it's just that…

1541
01:31:02,081 --> 01:31:03,791
I always think of you.

1542
01:31:03,875 --> 01:31:06,878
And I always listen to your podcasts.

1543
01:31:07,920 --> 01:31:11,048
The reason why I'm here…

1544
01:31:11,132 --> 01:31:12,925
How do I say this?

1545
01:31:13,009 --> 01:31:15,553
Ben, I want to tell you that…

1546
01:31:16,220 --> 01:31:17,305
Uh…

1547
01:31:18,514 --> 01:31:22,143
[in Victoria's voice] I'm giving you
a second chance for us to be okay.

1548
01:31:23,978 --> 01:31:24,979
How did you do that?

1549
01:31:25,813 --> 01:31:27,440
Is that what you want?

1550
01:31:27,982 --> 01:31:30,568
Well, it's up to you.

1551
01:31:31,068 --> 01:31:34,030
But if you don't want to,
then I'll just leave.

1552
01:31:34,614 --> 01:31:37,325
There's no problem if you want us to talk

1553
01:31:37,408 --> 01:31:38,910
and fix things.

1554
01:31:39,911 --> 01:31:42,496
See? It's meant to be.

1555
01:31:43,289 --> 01:31:45,750
Look, it’s Valentine’s Day.

1556
01:31:46,959 --> 01:31:48,836
Valentine’s Day?

1557
01:31:48,920 --> 01:31:50,671
Babe, it's not yet Valentine's Day.

1558
01:31:51,464 --> 01:31:52,381
From what I know,

1559
01:31:52,965 --> 01:31:55,968
it's National Heart Attack
Awareness Day today.

1560
01:31:57,970 --> 01:32:00,097
[mascot] Let us take care of our hearts.

1561
01:32:00,806 --> 01:32:03,309
Let’s avoid eating fatty foods.

1562
01:32:04,268 --> 01:32:07,813
Oh, sorry.
I don't have a sense of time anymore.

1563
01:32:08,523 --> 01:32:09,690
[in English] Sorry.

1564
01:32:11,984 --> 01:32:13,402
Before we settle our problems,

1565
01:32:14,111 --> 01:32:15,905
what is Humberto to you?

1566
01:32:15,988 --> 01:32:17,156
Well, it's…

1567
01:32:18,074 --> 01:32:19,575
Humberto is here!

1568
01:32:19,659 --> 01:32:21,619
[tense music playing]

1569
01:32:23,287 --> 01:32:24,372
Victoria!

1570
01:32:25,039 --> 01:32:27,833
This guy! He is Humberto!
The villain in my life!

1571
01:32:28,501 --> 01:32:29,502
Dude, relax!

1572
01:32:29,585 --> 01:32:30,628
Wait. Wait.

1573
01:32:31,170 --> 01:32:32,296
Is that him?

1574
01:32:32,380 --> 01:32:33,714
Wait.

1575
01:32:33,798 --> 01:32:36,550
Humberto is my boss.

1576
01:32:36,634 --> 01:32:38,469
-Your boss?
-Humberto.

1577
01:32:39,178 --> 01:32:41,556
I’ve been through a lot,

1578
01:32:41,639 --> 01:32:43,391
and you always get in my way.

1579
01:32:43,474 --> 01:32:44,642
I'm Benedict.

1580
01:32:46,727 --> 01:32:48,563
[girl] Love, let's go!

1581
01:32:48,646 --> 01:32:50,231
Hey, love.

1582
01:32:50,314 --> 01:32:51,983
Wait. I'm confused.

1583
01:32:52,775 --> 01:32:54,485
-He's your boss.
-Yes.

1584
01:32:54,568 --> 01:32:56,487
But he wanted you
to go to Singapore, right?

1585
01:32:56,571 --> 01:32:57,863
He was tearing us apart.

1586
01:32:57,947 --> 01:32:58,781
What?

1587
01:32:59,949 --> 01:33:02,410
Stella is Humberto's girlfriend.

1588
01:33:02,493 --> 01:33:03,577
Not me.

1589
01:33:04,370 --> 01:33:06,914
[Humberto] Dude, you're lucky
to have her as girlfriend.

1590
01:33:06,998 --> 01:33:08,165
She loves you so much.

1591
01:33:08,249 --> 01:33:12,044
-She even refused the offer for Singapore.
-That's why I got promoted.

1592
01:33:12,128 --> 01:33:13,796
I'll fly to Singapore next week.

1593
01:33:14,880 --> 01:33:18,009
-Is it true, babe? You're not leaving?
-Yes…

1594
01:33:18,092 --> 01:33:20,845
Yes. That's what I was talking about.

1595
01:33:20,928 --> 01:33:24,098
-We will be together.
-Yes!

1596
01:33:25,516 --> 01:33:26,892
Hey, I miss you.

1597
01:33:30,062 --> 01:33:33,482
[Benedict] What happened to the lights?
Direk! Direk?

1598
01:33:33,566 --> 01:33:34,608
What about our kiss?

1599
01:33:35,443 --> 01:33:36,485
Direk!

1600
01:33:36,569 --> 01:33:38,738
[techno music playing]

1601
01:35:08,953 --> 01:35:10,037
[man] Excuse me.

1602
01:35:10,121 --> 01:35:12,790
I heard you're the only one
who can help me.

1603
01:35:13,416 --> 01:35:15,835
Why are you here?

1604
01:35:17,086 --> 01:35:18,754
I'm so sick of being handsome.

1605
01:35:19,463 --> 01:35:21,048
I wanna go back to my old self.

1606
01:35:26,429 --> 01:35:30,057
[lively music playing]
